      • build

        public ADManufacturerSpecific build(int length,
                           int type,
                           byte[] data,
                           int companyId)
        Description copied from interface: ADManufacturerSpecificBuilder
        Build an AD structure of type Manufacturer Specific Data.
        Specified by:
        build in interface ADManufacturerSpecificBuilder
        Parameters:
        length - The length of the AD structure. It is the value of the first octet of the byte sequence of the AD structure.
        type - The AD type. The value is always 0xFF which represents Manufacturer Specific Data.
        data - The AD data. It is the third and following octets of the byte sequence of the AD structure. Note that the value of the first two bytes represents the company ID.
        companyId - The company ID. It is the value generated by interpreting the third and fourth octets of the byte sequence of the AD structure in little endian.
        Returns:
        An instance of ADManufacturerSpecific or its subclass. If the builder fails to build an instance, null should be returned.
